| Start session | `con <- dbConnect(duckdb())` then `CREATE VIEW ga4 AS ...` |
| Count events | `SELECT event_name, COUNT(*) FROM ga4 GROUP BY 1` |
| Filter by date | `WHERE event_date BETWEEN '20210101' AND '20210131'` |
| Unnest event_params | `CROSS JOIN UNNEST(event_params) AS ep(key, value)` |
| Access nested field | `device.category`, `geo.country` |
| End session | `dbDisconnect(con)` |

The key principle: **BigQuery is touched once, everything else is local.** DuckDB reads only the Parquet partitions your `WHERE event_date` clause needs, so a one-week query on 3 months of data only scans \~23% of the files.

